## Example 3 — Find Diagonal Lengths Using the Bisecting Property

The diagonals of parallelogram $PQRS$ intersect at point $M$. If $PM = 9$ and $QM = 6$, find the full lengths of the diagonals.

### Step 1: Apply the Diagonal Bisecting Property

The diagonals of a parallelogram bisect each other, so $M$ is the midpoint of both diagonals.

$$PM = MR = 9 \quad \text{so} \quad PR = PM + MR = 9 + 9 = 18$$

$$QM = MS = 6 \quad \text{so} \quad QS = QM + MS = 6 + 6 = 12$$

### Step 2: State the Answer

✅ Answer: $PR = 18$ and $QS = 12$.

