## Example 4 — Algebraic Problem with Parallelogram Angles

In parallelogram $JKLM$, $\angle J = (3x + 10)°$ and $\angle K = (5x - 30)°$. Find all angle measures.

### Step 1: Use Consecutive Angles Are Supplementary

$\angle J$ and $\angle K$ are consecutive angles, so they sum to 180°.

$$(3x + 10) + (5x - 30) = 180$$

### Step 2: Solve for x

$$8x - 20 = 180$$

$$8x = 200$$

$$x = 25$$

### Step 3: Find Each Angle

$$\angle J = 3(25) + 10 = 75 + 10 = 85°$$

$$\angle K = 5(25) - 30 = 125 - 30 = 95°$$

$$\angle L = \angle J = 85°$$

$$\angle M = \angle K = 95°$$

### Step 4: Verify

$$85° + 95° + 85° + 95° = 360° \checkmark$$

Consecutive pairs: $85° + 95° = 180°$.

✅ Answer: The angles are $\angle J = 85°$, $\angle K = 95°$, $\angle L = 85°$, $\angle M = 95°$.

